fll-live-initscripts (2.0.48) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - define XSERVER_PCIIDS_DIR
    - int printxdriver() -> char *lookup_xorg_dvr_for(), function now returns a
      point to string that is the xorg driver to be used
    - instead of sscanf, strip the .ids extension from current enrty->d_name
      with strrchr plus a pointer trick
    - add a few code comments
    - remove extra / in filename seperator
    - add some commented debug printf's
    - define VGA_CLASS as 0x0300

  [ Stefan Lippers-Hollmann ]
  * include strings.h, needed for strncasecmp().
  * fix fopen call to match ISO C90.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Fri, 09 Nov 2007 02:17:41 +0100

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.47) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add bin/fll_xserver_discover.c, a C port using libpci to detect VGA
    hardware. It is currently unused. Requires pciutils-dev and zlib1g-dev.
  * Add Build-dep of pciutils-dev and zlib1g-dev.
  * Remove perl version of fll_xserver_discover, no longer suggest
    discover1-data.
  * fll-live-xorgconfig becomes arch: all, adapt debian/rules to build
    fll_xserver_discover.
  * Export XMODULE and not XDRIVER.
  * Build-Dep on asciidoc and docbook, use asciidoc to convert ascii txt
    source to troff at build time. Add xsltproc, docbook-xml and docbook-xsl
    too.
  * Port existing manpages to ascii text, add ascii manpage source for
    fll_xserver_discover(8).
  * Add ascii manpage source for fll_xorgconfig(8).
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - hardcode the Screen option in Serverlayout section, save 6 lines of
      obsolete code
    - remove template support for Depth's 1 and 4
    - remove the obsolete files, module and dri templates

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 06 Nov 2007 15:56:57 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.46) unstable; urgency=low

  * start with the lazy ass mirror selection adaption, switching to easier
    methods through sources.list.d requires additional knowledge about
    selected suites and components and will be dereffered just like random
    sidux mirror selection post pre2.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sat, 03 Nov 2007 23:04:52 +0100

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.45) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - don't specify the device section to use in the screen section, the first
      device section listed will be selected by xserver-xorg-core >= 2:1.4-3
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - nv devices are falling back to vesa way too often. In this case grep the
      boardname for 4xxx, 5xxx, 6xxx, 7xxx generation device descriptions and
      force use of nv driver

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Thu, 01 Nov 2007 20:25:42 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.44) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - my synopsis about xresprobe reporting erraticly sorted list of
      resolutions was wrong, therefore sort_modes() has been removed
    - take the left most resolution value that xresprobe returns as preferred
      (this is arguable, xresprobe sometimes returns a too high mode than can
      be preferred by a human eye) and discard any modes in the list with X or
      Y axis values greater than that of the preferred
  * fll_fshelper:
    - depend on File::Slurp, use slurp to read removable attribute file that
      udev exports to sysfs in device_is_removable() function

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 30 Oct 2007 16:45:42 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.43) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - force colordepth of 16 for vesa, this helps with antiquated graphics
      chipsets.
  * fll_fshelper:
    - don't include a name of tool that goes missing after live-cd in a
      persistent configfile.
  * fll-cpufreq:
    - use -type & -name options to locate arch specific cpufreq dir rather
      than -path.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 29 Oct 2007 11:15:29 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.42) unstable; urgency=low

  * don't depend on dctrl-tools.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 28 Oct 2007 16:01:09 +0100

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.41) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - xresprobe sometimes returns a list of modes in a _non_ descending
      order, add sanitize_modes() to combat this phenomenon. From the string
      of probed resolutions, prefer the left most resolution, discarding all
      other higher resolutions from the rest of the string.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Fri, 26 Oct 2007 19:15:45 +1000

