fll-live-initscripts (2.0.20) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix poor grammar in debian/copyright.
  * Purge fll-EXAMPLE, we have enough of them now.
  * fll_analyze_initscripts.1:
    - remove ref to --apply option, it was unused, and now absent.
  * fll-cpufreq:
    - do not write cpufreq module to /etc/modules, this is annoying with
      persistency. If this turns out to be painful, we may be better served
      hacking the cpufrequtils package initscript into something useable
  * fll-network:
    - refactor netdev detection into simple shell function, get rid of perl
      heavyweight
    - split out code that writes to e/n/i, we may use it for alternative
      routines later
    - move check for existing config out of write_dhcp_to_eni to loop that
      forks the link probe
    - write a new /e/n/i on each boot, we may provide a persistent hook in the
      future
    - extend write_dhcp_to_eni to accept auto|allow-hotplug as first arguments
    - don't do anything if network-manager is installed

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Thu, 11 Oct 2007 18:41:38 +1000

