fll-live-initscripts (2.0.13) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - when xmodule= cheatcode is used, do the xresprobe probe with that module
      as argument too, as this is almost always used to force the vesa driver
    - don't define XKBVARIANT for specific languages here, that is the job of
      fll-locales
    - add note above $XDEPTH handling that x_res_probe may also export this
      variable (xresprobe "depth:" field).
    - add rate and mode cheatcode aliases
